    Scope and Contents
PAC 475, Intersession:  Science and Human Values (January 10-14, 1977) consists of pamphlets and audiocassettes.  This Intersession examined the discoveries of science research in astronomy and cosmology, physics, ecology, and human genetics, their impact on human values, and their implications for  public policy as well as the processes, methodologies and ethics of science.
(See also J51/9 Course materials;  Science and Human Values)
